        </faultConnector>
        <inputReference>ContactPointPhoneToCreate</inputReference>
    </recordCreates>
    <recordCreates>
        <description>Creates an Individual record based on the info from Contact record</description>
        <name>CreateIndividual</name>
        <label>Create Individual for Contact</label>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <connector>
            <targetReference>PrepareContactRecordForUpdate</targetReference>
        </connector>
        <faultConnector>
            <targetReference>AddCreateIndividualErrorLog</targetReference>
        </faultConnector>
        <inputReference>IndividualRecordToCreate</inputReference>
    </recordCreates>
    <recordDeletes>
        <description>In case if Contact cannot be updated with IndividualId we want to roll back the creation of the Individual record.

As of Feb 26, Roll Back elements is not available in this flow. This element is a workaround to achieve the same behavior. &quot;Custom Error&quot; element doesn&apos;t work properly in Async Path (or in Fault Path) and in case if Contact update is failed we want to roll back creation of Individual. This element handles success and fail scenario: if it gets deleted - roll back has happened, if deletion has failed - unhandled exception is thrown and the transaction is rolled back.

NOTE: Since &quot;Delete Individual&quot; can fail and we are ok with that - ensure that logging method is always ahead of this element.</description>
        <name>DeleteIndividual</name>
        <label>Delete Individual</label>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <inputReference>IndividualRecordToCreate</inputReference>
    </recordDeletes>
    <recordUpdates>
        <description>Updates the triggering Contact with created Individual ID.</description>
        <name>UpdateContactWithIndividualId</name>
        <label>Update Contact with Individual Id</label>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <connector>
            <targetReference>IsContactEmailNull</targetReference>
        </connector>
        <faultConnector>
            <targetReference>AddUpdateContactErrorLog</targetReference>
        </faultConnector>
        <inputReference>ContactWithPopulatedIndividualId</inputReference>
    </recordUpdates>
    <start>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <doesRequireRecordChangedToMeetCriteria>true</doesRequireRecordChangedToMeetCriteria>
        <filterFormula>{!$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName} = &quot;Member_Contact&quot;</filterFormula>
        <object>Contact</object>
        <recordTriggerType>CreateAndUpdate</recordTriggerType>
        <scheduledPaths>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>IsIndividualIdNull</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <pathType>AsyncAfterCommit</pathType>
        </scheduledPaths>
        <triggerType>RecordAfterSave</triggerType>
    </start>
    <status>Active</status>
